Have never delt with wild rabbits - have about 60 rabbits
in my barn.
The one suggestion I would have is to let it get use to the
feed in the field before you turn it lose - feeding it hay
and pulling some grass fron the field and letting it eat it.
I know a sudden change in diet can kill a rabbit. Several
day of letting it eat some hay and field grass will help.

Guessing - time of day to turn lose - early in the day - to
avold night stalkers.

